< review>
Just found my experience unremarkable in every way. The service was mediocre. Literally no interaction or explanation of the wines. They just bring it to the table. Wine was decent but pricey for my 1oz tasters. what I found particularly underwhelming- choice of glassware and plating. Just blah.... For a vineyard that produces wines with good marks, this tasting was not what I was hoping for.</review>

<gmap_id>0x8085ac1cded34af7:0x6f3e406a29a76617< /gmap_id>< Review>
My husband and I first visited Roche winery in the early 90's when we lived in Detroit. On a yearly basis, we would order a case of the tamerex wine to remind us of the good time we had back then. Since moving to Florida 8 yrs. ago, we haven't  placed an order. Last week, after reminiscing about Roche winery, we called and placed an order.  We asked Dave, who took our order, to email the shipping number so we could track our order. (The shipping cost $63.00). We made this request 3 times. Although he said he would, Dave never extended this small courtesy. This will be the last order we will ever purchase from Roche. Perhaps $360 is not a lot of money to Dave or Roche wineries, but it is to us. I could've bought 2 cases of white merlot for  that price.
NEVER MORE!<//Review>

<Resp>None< /Resp>< text>
My boyfriend had always bragged about this place for their 75 cent pizza slice on Tuesdays (if I remember correctly) and came here ever since he was little, so I decided to give it a try. Ordered a medium pizza with pepperoni, sausage, and mushrooms. Man oh man, I never expected to get a good portion of toppings and the pizza was a perfect! Alot of pizza restaurants are stingy with how much toppings they put on your pizza, but this place gives you the perfect amount. I love the crust and overall, it was pure hot goodness! Service is great and they give a variety of deals! MUST COME!<//text>

<name>Richardj Wickberg</name>< Review>
I bought a coolant/oil filtration system for my 6.0 powerstroke and the fit and finish was outstanding. The directions were some of the best I've ever used with very clear color pictures on the thick paper so if oil or coolant got on them you could just wipe it off. The only issue I had was that quite a few items were missing from the kit, all the hose clamps, 2 bolts for the filter housing block and a hose retaining clamp. Luckily I have a shop and had all these things anyway but just make sure to check before you install this!<//Review>

matthew rountree</name>
< date>
1554697682540< /date>
< Rating>
4</Rating>
< review>
They said it couldn't be done

Actually putting the Sinister oil bypass kit on a ram 6.7 with dual radiators it's pretty simple. All it took was putting a shim under the third bolt position and tipping the filter down far enough so that it didn't distort the hoses going to the radiator it works fine but it would be a lot better if they add two or three inches to the discharge line because I could have tipped it more and still had room to get the canister on from the bottom except I was starting to stretch the discharge line like a guitar string so I had to tip it back up thus somewhat distorting the radiator hoses.

I didn't really care what it was going to take to put the kit in ... it was going to go in because I don't really want to run soot though my bearings and as it turned out it was very simple to do .

So hopefully they'll figure out that all they have to do is lower the point of contact with the hoses and extend the discharge line to make it just as easy to put on a dual radiator system as a standard radiator system</review>

None</pics>

< review>
I have purchased a number of items from Sinister Diesel. The most major purchase I made was a complete solutions package for my 07 6.0 Powerstroke. To be honest, I was a little apprehensive to take this route rather than OEM, but in hindsight I couldn‚Äôt be any more pleased. All the parts were of great quality and they have held up great. About a year after replacing the head gaskets and other major parts included with the kit, I had a small problem with the o-ring seals on one standpipe. I contacted Sinister Diesel and their customer service took the care to replace the parts as quickly as they were able. The parts are great, the customer service is great, and the knowledge that these parts are made right in here the USA all help me to feel that I will go through Sinister Diesel for all of my truck‚Äôs needs. I couldn‚Äôt be any more pleased with the experiences I have had with them so far. They are a little more expensive compared to the knockoff items other companies offer, but in my opinion, it is well worth the extra money.</review>

< review>
Do not use the web chat/email service.  They will not respond to that.  You will need to call, wait up to 10 minutes for a live helpful response to your questions.  If you need mike from the fab shop, wait another 10 minutes after the initial wait.  Have your cell phone fully charged.

All but one of my orders had fast delivery and quality parts.  Either made by sinister diesel or by others.

My only concern is of the weld integrity of their headers.  However, I was reassured after sending pictures and another phone call, that there have been no header cracking or other failures.  That these were full penetration welds and that they have a life time warranty.  We may find out more with this product.  I do not have that comfy feeling on the header quality.  The lack of fillet welds worries me.

Otherwise, no issues yet.  Thanks for the help guys</review>

<rating>5</rating><Review>I have ordered from Sinister twice. Both times, no problems. Both were web orders, and both shipped quickly (items delivered inside of a week, but I am in CA.). I've never dealt with anyone in person, or on the phone. Maybe they are jerks in person, but I would never know. They've had what I needed, so I'll continue to be a customer until there's a reason not to be.
Being in the retail business myself, I see a lot of these 1 star reviews among a sea 5 star reviews and there is always more to the story than the complainer let's on. Usually the customer is just a pain in the a$$ and will never be happy. Many times the customer is just flat out wrong, but the internet has given every whiner a voice, so there you go. Frequently it is actually the distributor or manufacturer that is the reason parts are delayed. No company is perfect, and sometimes problems occur. That doesn't mean a company is bad or dishonest. You'll just have to give them a shot and find out for yourself. I'm happy with them, if that makes any difference.<//Review>< pics>

<name>Chad Holder<//name><time>1554073934267</time><response>None</response>< Review>
Great experience with Sinister Diesel!
I ordered a an AMSOIL By-Pass filter kit for my 2006 Dodge Ram 3500 5.9L Cummins. My oil is as clean as ever. Have not conducted an Oil Analysis yet but plan to soon. This kit is amazing and looks real good under the hood. Only point of concern I had was the vibration and what effects it will eventually have on the filter but, the bracket is welded with quality!
When I did initially received the order it did heave the wrong filter head. It had the coolant filter head instead. I called Sinister Diesel up told them the issue and they mailed the right filter head overnight!
Thank you Sinister diesel!</Review>

<Name>Michael Cooper<//Name><time>1494452860084< /time><rate>5<//rate>< Review>
2007 F350 4X4 had installed 50hp boost on injectors and 100hp on FICM. I then was not breathing enough so installed SINISTER intake all pipes and a stainless racing exhaust 5" from turbo back. She runs like a banshee Indian on fire. My exhaust has muffler so much quieter than most (wife likes dat). I love all that blue under the hood. Told my wife I may take the hood off, LOL. It's lots of fun to drive.</Review>

Great service, great parts!</Review>
<name>Miranda Murphy< /name><Time>1556901924603< /Time><user>112172680361785421240<//user></record></dataset><record>
< Text>
I had a major melt down with my12 year old 2005 6.0 Power Stroke Diesel Excursion. Oil Cooler ruptured internally and pumped 4 quarts of oil into my radiator. I went to the Web site for Sinister Diesel and did some initial research and then contacted Eric by Phone. He was most helpful and I ordered a package deal. It had an updated Oil Cooler, new design EGR Cooler, upgraded Stand Pipes, Dummy Plugs, HPOP update kit, upgraded Turbo Oil Feed Line, Drain Tube, Blue Spring kit, Bypass Oil filter kit, Bypass Coolant filter kit and all the necessary filters, gaskets and hardware to get the job done right the first time. I had looked elsewhere for most of this stuff, but the packaging and completeness of there kits are second to none and the price was right. I feel my 6.0 PSD should last me a long time now.< /Text>

< review>
Ordered a redesigned, Stainless steel EGR Cooler for my Duramax, web site and ordering process was all very straight forward and professional. Unfortunately for me Sinister is very professional and had to cancel my order because I live in California and their EGR Coolers are not yet CARB approved. The next day I confirmed that my money was refunded. In the end, I cant really complain about anything other than the Govt got in my way. I found a work around later on down the road so - I would recommend Sinister.</review>
